Making sure they get enough quality sleep should be a secret weapon for students to fight stress, fatigue and anxiety, he added, even to avoid gaining weight, since sleep deprivation puts the brain in sleep mode and makes students always hungry.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian studying Chemistry and Physical Biology, helped Professor Czeisler design the course, after having attended one of his classes in his senior year during his freshman year at Harvard.
